The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 September is 3,431 (397.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 September, there were 115 new confirmed cases (13.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 September, there were 112 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 3% (3 extra cases).
